{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2710"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of electric motors, generators, transformers and electricity distribution and control apparatus"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2710"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :electrical-equipment/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :electrical-safety :grid-reliability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :electrical-equipment-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "ElecEquipAdvisor ⊣ Electrical Equipment Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for electric motor, generator, transformer and
 electricity distribution/control apparatus manufacturing (winding/
 insulation/assembly/testing lines producing finished electrical
 equipment) -- not direct winding/assembly/test-bench-equipment control
 authority and not electrical-safety-certification authority (e.g.
 UL/CE/IEC compliance mark). Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Twelve concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct winding/assembly/test-bench-equipment control),
 permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent safety-certification-
 authority block (this actor never self-issues an electrical-safety
 compliance mark), independent equipment verification/registration
 before maintenance scheduling, independent batch verification/
 registration before shipment coordination, independent shipment-
 quantity recompute against the batch's own logged production
 quantity, double-schedule guard, product-type validation, dielectric-
 test-voltage plausibility validation, and defect-rate plausibility
 validation. Safety-concern flagging (insulation-failure/electrical-
 safety/high-voltage-test-hazard) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant
 supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
